---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Terms of Service — Tobiloba Adeyemo"
  description="Terms of service for security audit and consulting engagements with Tobiloba Adeyemo."
>
  <section>
    <div class="container prose">
      <p class="kicker">Legal</p>
      <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="muted">Last updated: 12 June 2026</p>

      <h2>Services</h2>
      <p>
        I provide security assessment and consulting services as described on this website.
        Specific scope, deliverables, and timelines for each engagement are confirmed in writing
        before work begins.
      </p>

      <h2>Authorization</h2>
      <p>
        Security audits are performed only on systems you own or are explicitly authorized to have
        assessed. By engaging my services you confirm you have the authority to grant that access.
      </p>

      <h2>Payment</h2>
      <p>
        Prices are listed in South African Rand (ZAR). Payment terms are agreed per engagement
        before work begins.
      </p>

      <h2>Confidentiality</h2>
      <p>
        Findings, credentials, and business information encountered during an engagement are
        treated as confidential and are not shared with third parties.
      </p>

      <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>
        Audits are point-in-time assessments. They reduce risk; they cannot guarantee that a
        system is free of vulnerabilities. To the maximum extent permitted by law, my liability is
        limited to the fees paid for the engagement concerned.
      </p>

      <h2>Governing law</h2>
      <p>These terms are governed by the laws of the Republic of South Africa.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
